Project.Title: SCLC LCNEC FFPE LMD
Project.Description: Small-cell lung carcinoma (SCLC) and large-cell neuroendocrine lung carcinoma (LCNEC) are high-grade lung neuroendocrine tumors (NET). However, comparative protein expression within SCLC and LCNEC remains unclear. Here, protein expression profiles were obtained via mass spectrometry-based proteomic analysis.

Contact.Name: Toshihide Nishimura
Contact.Affiliation: St. Marianna University School of Medicine

Relation.Keywords: lung cancer, FFPE tissues, laser-microdissection, exploratory LC/MS analysis

Sample.title: SCLC LCNEC FFPE LMD
Sample.note: This samp is cancerous cells obtained by laser-microdissection.

Enzyme_Mod.title: MS-based proteomic Analysis of cancerous cells laser-micrdissected from FFPE tissue specimens of small-cell lung cancinoma and large-cell neudoendocrine lung carinoma
Enzyme_Mod.note: Proteins were extracted and digested with trypsin using Liquid Tissue® MS Protein Prep kits (OncoPlex Diagnostics Inc., Rockville, MD, USA) according to the manufacturer’s protocol: Prieto DA, Hood BL, Darfler MM, Guiel TG, Lucas DA, Conrads TP, et al. Liquid Tissue™: proteomic profiling of formalin-fixed tissues. BioTechniques 2005;38:S32-5.
